This paper focuses on designing and evaluating a convergence layer for Information Centric Networking (ICN) in low power lossy networks, which is a subfield of networked systems and communication. Therefore, cs.NI (Networked Systems and Communication) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses compression schemes and adaptation of packets, which are related to cryptography (cs.CR) and information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper evaluates the compatibility of ICN with IPv6, which falls under the category of computer architecture (cs.AR) and systems and control (cs.SY).
